The paper proposes a deep neural network for object tracking that uses natural language as supervised information and constructs a graph to represent pairwise relationships among training samples. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of deep learning techniques for feature representation and classification suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on tracking benchmark datasets, indicating that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
